                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1123 Lincheng/166: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-06-22T10:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1923—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 22—4:58 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>233. My 223, June 14, 5 p.m. Committee’s report also includes among claims for
                    compensation an item for refund of expenses incurred in providing for the
                    captives the means of subsistence and relief. So far as known all such
                    provisions were made by the American Chamber of Commerce, Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
